---
title: topkg porting
author: mirageos devs
abstract: status of topkg ported libraries
tags: active project, core, help needed
---

Topkg is [the transitory OCaml package builder](http://erratique.ch/software/topkg/doc/Topkg), well-designed and slicker than oasis.

It also enforces naming policies for metadata (LICENSE, README, CHANGES, etc), and nicely integrates documentation and metadata retrieval with [odig](http://erratique.ch/software/odig).

## Libraries ported

- see [list](http://opam.ocaml.org/packages/topkg/)

## Libraries need porting

- [dns](https://github.com/mirage/ocaml-dns) [PR](https://github.com/mirage/ocaml-dns/pull/126)
- [io-page](https://github.com/mirage/io-page)
- [vmnet](https://github.com/mirage/ocaml-vmnet)
- [cstruct](https://github.com/mirage/ocaml-cstruct)
- [mirage-xen / -unix](https://github.com/mirage/mirage-platform) (@avsm might have somewhere branches)
- [mirage-tcpip](https://github.com/mirage/mirage-tcpip) [@avsm has an outdated branch](https://github.com/avsm/mirage-tcpip/tree/topkg)
- [mirage-net-xen](https://github.com/mirage/mirage-net-xen)
- [mirage-block-xen](https://github.com/mirage/mirage-block-xen)
- [mirage-block-unix](https://github.com/mirage/mirage-block-unix)
- [xen-evtchan](https://github.com/mirage/ocaml-evtchn)
- [xen-gnt](https://github.com/mirage/ocaml-gnt)
- [mirage-block-ccm](https://github.com/sg2342/mirage-block-ccm)
- see also [errors from odig](http://docs.mirage.io/ocamldoc_/#errors)
